verbose_text: Thymidylate synthase (TYMS), a 5-FU target, requires 5,10-methylenetetrahydrofolate (5,10-methylene-THF), a folate co-factor, as a methyl group donor and methylates deoxyuridine monophosphate (dUMP) to become deoxythymidine monophosphate (dTMP).
